<h4>Support for Rules on Config Repositories (Pipeline as Code)</h4>

In order to provide fine-grained access control over the entities that are created by a config repository, GoCD adds support for defining rules on config repositories that specifies which environments, pipeline groups, pipelines the repository can refer to.
Please refer to the [Specifying rules on Config Repository](https://docs.gocd.org/20.2.0/advanced_usage/pipelines_as_code.html#specifying-rules) for more information.


<h4>Changes to SSL Support</h4>
There are important changes to how GoCD handles SSL support. If you are upgrading to GoCD 20.2.0, agents will have to be reconfigured to connect to the server. Please read the [GoCD SSL Changes](https://github.com/gocd/gocd/issues/7872) for more information.


